104	\begin{lemma}[Stalkwise detection of exactness for sheaves of modules — mathematical statement only]
105	  \label{lem:sheafOfModules_exact_iff_stalkwise}
106	  A short complex of sheaves of $\mathcal R$-modules is exact iff its image under each stalk functor $(-)_x$ is exact in the corresponding category of modules at $x$. This transfers an exactness statement on the sheaf side to a pointwise statement on the ring-of-stalks side, where Mathlib's $\mathrm{KaehlerDifferential}$ exactness becomes directly applicable. \emph{Not yet formalised in Lean} (pending an upstream Mathlib formulation of \texttt{SheafOfModules.stalkFunctor} and its exactness-reflection theorem).
107	\end{lemma}
